==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wentletrap
<hw>Wen"tle*trap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>wenteltrap</ets> a winding staircase; cf. G.
<ets>wendeltreppe</ets>.]</ety> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <def>Any one of
numerous species of elegant, usually white, marine shells of the genus
Scalaria, especially <spn>Scalaria pretiosa</spn>, which was formerly
highly valued; -- called also <altname>staircase shell</altname>. See
<er>Scalaria</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wep</ent>⟦br⟧
